      <!-- Operation -->
      <div id="operation" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4" style="font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', sans-serif;">Operation</h2>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The fuel or mineral oil is fed into the rotating bowl of the MAB-103 centrifuge. The bowl exerts a high g-force (8,500 Gs) on the process fluid. The centrifugal force causes rapid sedimentation of the solid particles down to 0.5 Microns.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          This separated sludge should be manually evacuated by the operator. The heavy phase (water) phase also settles out and exits the bowl through a separate outlet.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D]">
          As a manual-clean (solid-retaining) centrifuge, the MAB 103 requires periodic shutdown for the operator to disassemble the bowl, remove accumulated sludge, and reassemble. The frequency of cleaning depends on the solids loading of the process fluid. For relatively clean fluids such as turbine lube oil, cleaning intervals may be several weeks. For dirtier fuels or waste oils with higher solids content, more frequent cleaning cycles are necessary.
        </p>
      </div>

